    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What is Solution CMS Kit?",
        "answer": "Solution CMS Kit is a multi-tenant content management system that generates static websites from JSON configuration. Each tenant defines their own design tokens, pages, components, and features."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I create a new tenant?",
        "answer": "Copy template.json from the tenants/ directory, fill in your configuration values, and set EXPORT_TENANT_ID to your tenant ID when building."
      },
      {
        "question": "What components are available?",
        "answer": "The kit includes HeroCarousel, EventGrid, MenuDisplay, PhotoGallery, ContactSection, AboutSection, ServicesSection, CTASection, StructuredData, MembersGrid, MediaGallery, and more."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do features work?",
        "answer": "Features are boolean flags in the tenant config. Components can use featureGate to conditionally render based on enabled features. This allows each tenant to enable only what they need."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I add custom components?",
        "answer": "Yes. Register your component in the registry manifest and component map. The manifest acts as an allowlist — only registered types can be rendered from tenant JSON."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is the site exported?",
        "answer": "The kit uses Next.js static export. Run the build with EXPORT_TENANT_ID set to your tenant ID, and the output is a fully static site ready for any hosting provider."
      }
    ]
  },
